Fans of Sauti Sol have been disappointed after the band canceled their show for today citing covid-19 hitches. In a statement on Saturday, the band acknowledged that Kenyan's lives comes first before any other thing. "We were recently made aware that the event size does not comply with Covid-19 protocols,"the statement read. "We tried to mitigate the situation. However, we could not come into an agreement on the best way forward." The Sol family explained that with the infections rising all over the world, they can not afford to endanger the lives of Kenyans. "We shall be refunding the promoters, Tukutane entertainment, and Masshouse group the full fee duly paid without delay," they said. "It is disheartening and unfortunate but necessary and we hope to appear on stage again as soon as possible." More to follow